Creating a high-quality testing framework in Cypress that uses Docker, along with its capability to capture screenshots and save them, involves several steps. Below is a guide to help you set up such a framework. This guide assumes you have some familiarity with Cypress and Docker.

### Step 1: Set Up a New Project Directory

First, create a new directory for your project and navigate into it:

```bash
mkdir cypress-screenshot-tester
cd cypress-screenshot-tester
```

### Step 2: Create Dockerfile

